    NB: The end part (.DS_Store) you add ("> .gitignore)

 9. You can type (ls -a) to check the directory
 10.You can type (less .gitignore) to see some of the content of the gitignore
 11. When you want to come out of the folder of .gitignore type (Shift+:) and q
 12. You can type (ls -a) to know the structure of your current directory
 13. You can type (less .gitignore) to inspect the content of your gitignore file
 14. You can check status again (git status)
 15. You can stage your current files by typing (git add.)
 16. check status (git status)
 17.  You can delete any unwanted files from your project folder manually or use(rm -r [folder/file name])
 18.After deletion, come back to stage (git add .)
 19. Check status
 20. Now commit (git commit -m "initial commit)"
 21. check  ( git status)
 22. git log
 23. At this point you can add your github repository to your local repository by copying this command from your github account
 -git remote add origin https://github.com/felixatsuackuayi/Caleb30DaysOfJavaPracticals.git
 (enter and paste the below)
 -git branch -M master
  - git push -u origin master
  -You may have github window opened to login your github credential
 24. Now go to your github account and refresh.
 Now we need to make a commit but before that we can remove all other FOLDERS(provided those folders are not important,otherwise leave them)
 - to remove type (EX: rm -r testing) ..testing is the folder name
 14.Now commit to git by typing (git add .)